asap.realizer.planunit

Class MultiThreadedPlanPlayer<T extends TimedPlanUnit>

  • java.lang.Object
    • asap.realizer.planunit.MultiThreadedPlanPlayer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    PlanPlayer

    public class MultiThreadedPlanPlayer<T extends TimedPlanUnit>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PlanPlayer
    Runs a Plan in a separate thread. This is useful for TimedPlanUnits for which their execution is blocking (e.g. direct speech). For rapid execution of new TimedPlanUnits, the MultiThreadedPlanPlayer always has a thread available in which the plan can be run. Use shutdown to close the MultiThreadedPlanPlayer completely and get rid of its thread. The MultiThreadedPlanPlayer should not be reused after shutdown.
    Author:
    Herwin
